==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ginseng
<hw>Gin"seng</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Chinese.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A plant of the genus <gen>Aralia</gen>, the root
of which is highly valued as a medicine among the Chinese. The Chinese
plant (<spn>Aralia Schinseng</spn>) has become so rare that the American
(<spn>A. quinquefolia</spn>) has largely taken its place, and its root
is now an article of export from America to China. The root, when dry,
is of a yellowish white color, with a sweetness in the taste somewhat
resembling that of licorice, combined with a slight aromatic
bitterness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

